<br>
The current situation - making a wall, killing factional leaders of various groups like Hamas or Al Aksa Brigrade, suicide bombs, razing refugee camps, shutting down entire communities ad infinitum will not cease until real work is put into this.  <br>
<br>
This &quot;road map&quot; stuff are very small steps, but in order to create lasting peace I believe the US must force Israel to start making concrete steps.  Relocate the settlers living in occupied territory, get out of West Bank entirely and give the Palestinians some room to maneouvre, breathe, freedom, and respect and I promise that with time this endless cycle of violence will cease.<br>
<br>
It amazes how pro-Israeli the US population is (as a general).  I don't laud the Palestinian people they are at fault also, but the solution imo is in the hands of the US and for so many years so little has been done (especially under Bush).  I remain hopeful that this horrible region will one day find peace.<br>
